12 vitest cases authored before implementation:
- mount triggers fetch + sets types to merged list on resolve (AC-230-05 a)
- success merge preserves canonical order at the head + appends non-duplicate live entries (AC-230-05 b)
- fetch error surfaces error + falls back to canonical + loading false (AC-230-05 c)
- reload() refetches and updates cache (AC-230-05 d)
- cache hit on second mount with same connectionId does not re-call the Tauri wrapper (AC-230-05 e)
- display label rule — pg_catalog.X strips to X; <schema>.<name> for non-pg_catalog (AC-230-06)
- empty result — merged list == canonical exactly
- duplicate name — pg_catalog.varchar and canonical varchar yield single entry
- stale connectionId — original conn1 Promise resolves last, no state mutation for conn2
- concurrent mounts on same connectionId share one in-flight Promise (mock invoked once)
- invalidatePostgresTypesCache(connectionId) — fresh fetch on next mount (AC-230-11)
- defensive — entries with empty name or pg_toast schema dropped before merge

## §2 — `src/components/schema/CreateTableTypeCombobox.test.tsx` Sprint 230 describe — RED

4 new vitest cases authored under a fresh `describe("CreateTableTypeCombobox (Sprint 230 — typesSource prop)")` block. The combobox did not yet accept a `typesSource` prop, so the prop was silently ignored — the assertions that demanded a dynamic-source filter (e.g. `geometry` surfacing for query `geo`) failed because the canonical-list filter did not contain `geometry`.

```
 FAIL  src/components/schema/CreateTableTypeCombobox.test.tsx > CreateTableTypeCombobox (Sprint 230 — typesSource prop) > typesSource={...} filters the dynamic list (geo → geometry, varchar excluded)
AssertionError: expected [] to contain "geometry"
```

4 cases authored before implementation:
- typesSource={...} filters the dynamic list (geo → geometry, varchar excluded)
- typesSource omitted — canonical list path is used (back-compat)
- parametric default expansion intact when canonical bare 'varchar' is in the dynamic list (AC-230-09)
- non-parametric dynamic entry (geometry) commits verbatim

